The last film in the DCEU has arrived as The Flash starring Ezra Miller, Sasha Calle, and Michael Keaton has finally raced into theaters. Full of nostalgia, a bit of Flashpoint, and some bold choices, The Flash has people both raving about it and cursing its name. Where did we fall on that spectrum? Check out this episode of the Major Issues Podcast to find out!   If you can, please leave us a review on [ITunes](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by ComicBook Clique, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

